snippet: The protests are the closest that chaos has come to threatening the operations of the critical shipping artery over the last two years.
abstract: Thousands of demonstrators shut down administrative buildings of Suez Canal terminal in Port Said, Egypt, as part of general strike protesting death sentences handed down to 21 local soccer fans for their roles in a deadly riot in 2012; protests awaken the possibility of a threat to operations of a critical shipping artery.
lead_paragraph: The protests are the closest that chaos has come to threatening the operations of the critical shipping artery over the last two years.
